<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Privacy Policy</h1>
  
  <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
    <p class="mb-6">Last updated: February 22, 2026</p>
    
    <p>Nextgen-plaid ("we", "us", or "our") operates the nextgen-plaid web application. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our service.</p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect mobile phone numbers only from users who voluntarily provide them during account creation and explicitly consent to receive SMS notifications and alerts. We also collect Plaid-linked financial data (accounts, transactions, holdings) as authorized by you via Plaid OAuth.</p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>Mobile phone numbers are used solely to send informational SMS notifications about account sync status, security events, threshold alerts, and system updates. Financial data is used to provide personalized insights and simulations. We do not sell, share, or use your information for marketing or promotional purposes with third parties.</p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">SMS Notifications</h2>
    <p>By providing your phone number and checking the consent box during signup, you agree to receive recurring SMS from Nextgen-plaid. Message & data rates may apply. Frequency varies (not promotional spam). Reply <strong>HELP</strong> for help or <strong>STOP</strong> to unsubscribe. Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.</p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Data Security & Retention</h2>
    <p>We use encryption (attr_encrypted) and PostgreSQL row-level security. We retain data only as long as necessary for service provision. Contact support@nextgen-plaid.com for deletion requests.</p>
